# Requirements Document - Convenience Store Chain

## 1. Login Page
1.1 The system shall provide a login page with email and password fields.
1.2 The system shall display a red error message when invalid credentials are entered.
1.3 The system shall redirect to the dashboard upon successful login.
1.4 The system shall not allow access to any other page without a valid login token.

## 2. Dashboard
- The system shall display KPI cards showing total stores, total products, low-stock count, and recent orders count.
- The system shall display a bar chart of weekly sales using Chart.js.
- The system shall load dashboard data from the /api/dashboard endpoint.

## 3. Store Branch Management
- The system shall display a table of all store branches with name, address, manager, and status.
- The system shall provide an "Add Branch" button that opens a form to create a new branch.
- The system shall allow editing of an existing branch via an edit button.
- The system shall allow deactivating a branch (soft delete) via a deactivate button.
- The system shall refresh the branch table after any add/edit/deactivate action.

## 4. Inventory Management
- The system shall display a table of all products with name, current stock, threshold, and stock status badge.
- The system shall color‑code stock status: green (ok), yellow (low), red (critical).
- The system shall provide an "Add Product" button to create a new product.
- The system shall allow editing product details (name, price, threshold).
- The system shall provide a "Restock" button to increase stock quantity.
## 5. Employee Management
- The system shall display a list of employees with name, email, role, store branch, and status.
- The system shall provide a dropdown filter to show employees of a specific store branch.
- The system shall allow adding a new employee with validation (unique email, valid role).
- The system shall allow editing employee role, shift, or store assignment.
- The system shall allow deactivating an employee (soft delete).
## 6. Sales Reports
- The system shall provide toggle buttons for daily/weekly/monthly sales views.
- The system shall display a line chart of revenue over the selected period.
- The system shall show total revenue, total orders, and average order value.
- The system shall display a table of the 10 most recent orders.
- The system shall fetch sales data from the appropriate API endpoint based on the selected period.